---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Bio, career arc, and how to reach Joao V. Rocha — AV engineer at Sound Image / Clair Global, full-stack developer, Latin Grammy nominee."
  narrow
>
  <div class="about-head">
    <picture>
      <source
        type="image/webp"
        srcset="/images/me/victor-600.webp 1x, /images/me/victor-1200.webp 2x"
      />
      <img
        src="/images/me/victor-600.jpg"
        srcset="/images/me/victor-600.jpg 1x, /images/me/victor-1200.jpg 2x"
        alt="Victor Rocha — headshot"
        width="200"
        height="250"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
      />
    </picture>
    <h1>About</h1>
  </div>

  <p>
    I'm Joao V. Rocha — friends call me Victor. I've spent the last decade
    moving between three jobs that look unrelated until you stand back: live
    audio, operations on the floor, and the software stack behind both.
  </p>

  <p>
    Right now I'm an AV engineer at <a href="https://www.clairglobal.com">Sound
    Image</a> (a Clair Global company) in San Francisco, supporting clients
    like Apple and Dolby on Yamaha CL5, Dante, and Shure Axient rigs. On
    the side I build the software and hardware I think the operations floor is
    missing — most recently a Node + Postgres ops platform used in a retail
    store every day, and <strong>Shaddow</strong>, a 12 V automotive dock
    platform designed in <a href="https://www.flux.ai/p">Flux.ai</a> and KiCad.
  </p>

  <h2>The short career arc</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>2025 – present</strong> · AV engineer, Sound Image / Clair Global, San Francisco.</li>
    <li><strong>2024 – 2026</strong> · Stock manager + internal tools developer, Suitsupply SF. Built the Daily Operations Platform from scratch.</li>
    <li><strong>2015 – 2022</strong> · A1 / OPS coordinator, Vocal Livre (São Paulo). Toured Brazil at 100–25,000-attendee scale. Part of the production team for the Latin Grammy–nominated album <em>Temporal</em> (2023).</li>
    <li><strong>2017</strong> · A2 at Rock in Rio, 80,000 attendees.</li>
    <li><strong>2012 – 2020</strong> · IT support and AV operations at UNASP and Colégio Adventista IABC, Brazil.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What I work on now</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Live audio</strong> — FOH and monitor on Yamaha / DiGiCo / Avid, Dante-networked systems, Shure RF coordination.</li>
    <li><strong>Software</strong> — Node, Postgres, WebSockets, PWAs, MCP servers, the boring Linux deployment work that makes them stay up.</li>
    <li><strong>Hardware</strong> — <a href="/projects/shaddow">Shaddow</a>: 12 V automotive power and USB / CAN dock electronics in Flux.ai and KiCad.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Outside of work</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="/projects/van-conversion">Van conversion</a></strong> — a weekend build that doubles as the test bench Shaddow's hardware has to survive.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Languages, certs, schooling</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>English & Portuguese — native / bilingual. Spanish — elementary.</li>
    <li>Allen &amp; Heath dLive (May 2026) · Dante Level 1 (Apr 2026) · Shure Axient Digital / PSM · Networking for Audio Professionals.</li>
    <li>B.A. in Communication, Broadcasting Technology — UNASP, São Paulo, 2020.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="hire">Hire me</h2>
  <p>
    I'm open to AV engineering, full-stack, or operations + technology roles —
    San Francisco, hybrid, or remote. Best fit is a team where the person
    running cable and the person writing the code are allowed to be the same
    person.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:joaovorocha@gmail.com">joaovorocha@gmail.com</a></li>
    <li>LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/victordorocha/">linkedin.com/in/victordorocha</a></li>
    <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/joaovorocha">github.com/joaovorocha</a></li>
    <li><a href="/resume">Résumé (long-form)</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p class="meta" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
    This site is built with Astro, hosted on Cloudflare Pages, and written in
    markdown. Source at <a href="https://github.com/joaovorocha/victorocha.com">github.com/joaovorocha/victorocha.com</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .about-head img {
    width: 160px;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .about-head h1 {
    margin: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .about-head {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .about-head img {
      width: 140px;
      height: 175px;
    }
  }
</style>
